# Conflict Resolution Guidelines for Collaborative AI-Assisted Development

## Purpose
This rule is designed to help manage and resolve code conflicts during collaborative development, especially when multiple contributors (human or AI) are working on the same files or features.

## Branching Strategy
- All contributors must create feature branches (`feature/xyz`) or bugfix branches (`bugfix/xyz`) from the `main` or `develop` branch.
- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Regularly sync your branch with the base branch to minimize conflicts.

